info.title: Domino Data Lab APIs
info.description:
Domino has two types of APIs: **API Endpoints** which let you publish your code as a low-latency web service without any API design experience and the **Domino API** which lets you allow you to interact with your project's files and runs.

Two important notes:

1. Your API base URL will depend on your deployment of Domino. Replace the URL with the URL of your private Domino deployment (the site you visit in your browser when you use Domino)

2. To authenticate your requests, include your API Key (which you can find on your account page) with the header `X-Domino-Api-Key` .

commitId.description: The commit your API endpoint is bound to

file.description: The file your API endpoint is bound to

function.description: The function your API endpoint is bound to

version.description: The version of your API that was used

release.description: An object of key/value pairs describing the version of your API endpoint that responded to your request

requestId.description: A unique request ID assigned to your API request

result.description: The result of the function you bound to your API Endpoint. Will be either a JSON object/dictionary or array depending on what your function returns.

post.description:
Your API Endpoint is a wrapper on top of a function in your Domino-hosted code. The arguments to the API are the arguments to your function; the response from the API includes the return value from your function in the `result` object.

[Learn more about API Endpoint and Model Development](http://support.dominodatalab.com/hc/en-us/articles/204173149-API-Endpoints-Model-Deployment)

objectType.description: The type of object the API returned

uri.description: The URI that responded to your request

application/json.message: Run for project <username>/<project_name> started. You can view progress here: https://app.dominodatalab.com/<username>/<project_name/runs/553af271e4b0364c0f717b24

runId.description: The unique ID for the run that was just started

message.description: A human-readable message with a full link to view the status of your run

post.description: Start a run of a given script or command

command.description:
Array of strings making up your command. For example:

```python
        ["model.py", "dataset", "--sample", "2000"]
```

isDirect.description: A direct command is interpretted as a shell command; Domino doesn't try to infer a program to match your file type

title.description: An optional title for your run

tier.description: Identifier of the hardware tier to use

commitId.description: Revision at which to start the run

publishApiEndpoint.description: __This field will be deprecated in future versions.__ If true, the results of a successful run will be deployed to the project's active API Endpoint, if one exists

id.description: The unique ID for the run

number.description: The auto-increment number associated with the run

startingUserId.description: The ID of the user who started the run

queued.description: Milliseconds epoch time the run was added to the queue

started.description: Milliseconds epoch time the run started executing

completed.description: Milliseconds epoch time the run completed running

commitId.description: The commit hash of the project used to create the run

executor.description: The unique ID of the executor (compute node) the run was executed on

outputCommitId.description: The commit hash of the project post-run (look at files with this hash for the results)

title.description: Title of the run, if it was renamed

isArchived.description: Boolean denoting if the run was archived (hidden from the web interface)

postProcessedTimestamp.description: Milliseconds epoch time the run finished processing (this happens after the run has completed and includes saving the results back to the main project repo)

diagnosticStatistics.description: Object containing information about the run's [Diagnostic Statistics aka dominostats.json](http://support.dominodatalab.com/hc/en-us/articles/204348169-Run-Diagnostic-Statistics)

isCompleted.description: A boolean to denote if the run has completed or is still run. See `status` for success/failure status.

hardwareTierId.description: The hardware tier the run exectued on (new in v1.42)

get.description: Get the status of a run

parameters.name: run_id
parameters.description: The unique ID for the run

get.description: Get a list of files in a commit

parameters.name: commit_id
parameters.description: The commit ID of the version of the project you want files for

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The path for which you want files for

get.description: Get the contents of a file from the project

parameters.name: blob_id
parameters.description: The unique ID of the blob

path.description: Path within the project your file was saved to

lastModified.description: Milliseconds epoch time the file was last modified

size.description: The size of the file you just uploaded, in bytes

key.description: The blob ID for the file. Used by the 'Get a file' API

url.description: The full URL to the blob (this can be used to re-download the file)

put.description: Upload a file to your project

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: Where you want the file to be saved. (You can include forward slashes to upload files into folders that exist)

parameters.name: area
parameters.description: The type of object to search. Valid values are `project`, `run`, `file`, and `comment`

objectType.description: The type of object the API returned.
